description:
This API documentation describes how to interact with Untangle NGFW using JSON RPC over HTTP.

# Authentication
Each request your application sends must include an authentication token in the JSON object. To get a token, your application must send an administrative username and password via HTTP POST method to your server. If the authentication succeeds, the server responds with a JSON object containing an authentication token. 

# Formatting requests
Each request your applications sends to the JSON RPC interface must include the following parameters:
## Parameters

| Label        | Description           |
|-------------|-------------|
| id      | The identifier of a request. Each request must include a unique identifier. The server includes the corresponding identifier in each response to enable the requesting application to match the response with the request. |
| nonce   | The authentication token. Every request to the API must include this token in the body of the request.|

description: Join leaders from across the public sector technology community at the Trellix (formerly McAfee Enterprise and FireEye) Cybersecurity Summit as they discuss the evolving threat landscape, the new trends in securing against the most sophisticated attacks and how emerging technologies like XDR can help adaptively strengthen your security posture. Throughout the course of the summit, you’ll engage in conversations about the implementation of zero trust security across the public sector, evolving partnerships to strengthen threat intelligence, evolving the security operations center model, and much more.
title: Trellix | Cybersecurity Summit 2024

description:
The relentless growth of cyberattacks in today's digitally interconnected world has taken on new urgency for public sector officials, private sector leaders and those who operate the nation's critical infrastructure. The emergence of AI, combined with the growing resources of nation-state and criminal hackers, poses new dangers and risks that threaten not just individual privacy and corporate interests but also national security and global stability.

CyberTalks presents a powerful opportunity to hear from the leading voices at the intersection of government and the technology industry on the latest tactics to combat these new risks. CyberTalks also provides an invaluable forum for exchanging ideas and best practices on ways to bolster digital defenses and promote cyber resiliency.
title: CYBERTALKS 2024

description:
The federal government is in the midst of a digital transformation that has the potential to reinvent the way agencies provide citizen services and perform their most essential functions. Guided by the top priorities of the White House, leaders across the federal government are embracing modern technologies like AI and the cloud, fortifying cybersecurity by shifting to zero-trust architectures and prioritizing user experience in digital services. Yet, at this transformative moment in the federal technology landscape, intangibles like leadership, workforce development, innovation and cultural management remain key to navigating the massive shifts in how agencies serve their missions in the digital age.

Register now for FedTalks 2024 on June 5 at the Andrew Mellon Auditorium in downtown Washington, D.C. Hosted by FedScoop, FedTalks is the largest annual gathering of C-level executives, leaders and innovators from the government and tech communities. Now in its 15th year, FedTalks bring
title: FEDTALKS 2024

description:
As agencies face a constant wave of global and domestic threats, from cyberattacks to transnational crime, the strategic deployment of artificial intelligence has emerged as a critical capability for missions operating at the edge.
 
Join government leaders, AI experts and industry innovators at GDIT Emerge: AI on the Frontlines to hear how federal agencies stay ahead of threats by harnessing AI for tactical operations and strategic decision making in the field. Explore the balance between innovation and responsibility, how to successfully scale from AI pilot to real-world implementation, and the foundation needed to enable robust AI operations.
title: 2024 GDIT Emerge: AI on the Frontlines

description:
Operational technology powers critical systems across the nation, from the power grid to water facilities and pipelines. As OT integrates with IT networks, it faces new cyber risks that threaten national security. Recent reports of foreign adversaries infiltrating OT systems highlight the urgent need for resilience and defense.

Join top government leaders and industry experts to explore advanced strategies for protecting U.S. operational technology and critical infrastructure and understand the biggest threats facing these sectors today.
title: 2024 GDIT Emerge: Operational Technology Securing Our Nation’s Critical Infrastructure

description:
As technology evolves and the world around us becomes more digitally interconnected, real-time information sharing is key to staying ahead of emerging threats — from making decisions on battlefields abroad and keeping our nation safe to responding to emergencies and delivering humanitarian aid. The ability of defense, intelligence, and federal agencies to rapidly and securely share releasable information with partners ultimately determines mission success. 
 
 Join top government leaders and industry experts at GDIT Emerge: Information Sharing for Strategic Advantage to explore the evolution of data sharing, its importance in an increasingly digital world and the role of top federal agencies in driving its adoption. title: 2024 GDIT Emerge: Information Sharing for Strategic Advantage

description:
The role of AI in responding to security threats has taken on new urgency as agency leaders grapple with AI's emergence into mainstream business applications. However, threat actors are moving just as quickly to capitalize on AI to advance their attacks.

Secure your spot at the Google Public Sector Summit on Wednesday, October 16 to hear how agency and industry experts are approaching the widening intersection of AI and security. You'll hear from top leaders about where they're concentrating their AI efforts and gain important perspectives on how AI is being put to work in the public sector.
title: Google Public Sector Summit 2024
